   333	- Slice-output sampling tally: <count of slice-output sections sampled, capped at 3-5 per §5.2.5>
   334	- Source-reading tally: <count of source files read for fact-grounding, capped at 5 per §4.2>
   335	- Out-of-scope: <items the auditor noticed but did not pursue per §5.4>
   336	
   337	# §5. Non-binding disposition signal
   338	
   339	Auditor states why Logan might choose each plausible disposition (per §8). Auditor does not pick one; Logan disposes.
   340	
   341	- **Why Logan might choose commit-as-is:** <reasoning given findings>
   342	- **Why Logan might choose commit-with-addendum:** <reasoning given findings>
   343	- **Why Logan might choose revise-before-commit:** <reasoning given findings>
   344	```
   345	
   346	### §6.2 Step-2 (same-vendor stress) FINDINGS structure (if fired)
   347	
