.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/audit-spec.md:43:- The slice {N} output you're auditing (`.planning/gsd-2-uplift/exploration/0{N}-{slice-name}-output.md`)
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/audit-spec.md:44:- The slice {N} prompt (the slice-{N} spec at `.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/slice-0{N}-{slice-name}.md` plus the common preamble at `preamble.md`)
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/audit-spec.md:49:## Audit dimensions
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/audit-spec.md:53:### 1. Source verification
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/audit-spec.md:55:Spot-check 3-5 specific claims in the slice output against gsd-2 source.
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/audit-spec.md:58:- Are line citations correct (file exists; line says what slice claims)?
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/audit-spec.md:61:For each spot-check: cite slice's claim → gsd-2 source → verdict (verifiable / not-verifiable / wrong).
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/audit-spec.md:63:### 2. Completeness
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/audit-spec.md:65:Are there mechanisms / artifacts / patterns the slice missed within its own scope?
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/audit-spec.md:67:- Run targeted scans of gsd-2 source relevant to the slice (e.g., `find ~/workspace/projects/gsd-2-explore/ -type f -name "*.py" | head -50` or equivalent for the slice's domain).
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/audit-spec.md:68:- Spot-check for missed patterns. The slice's diagnostic questions define scope; check whether *all* scope is covered.
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/audit-spec.md:72:### 3. Framing-leakage detection
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/audit-spec.md:76:Specific patterns to flag if observed:
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/audit-spec.md:82:If found: quote verbatim; cite where in slice output; verdict on whether leakage is via the slice's prompt (which we control and could revise) or via cross-vendor reaching beyond forbidden-reading-list (more concerning).
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/audit-spec.md:84:### 4. Calibration discipline
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/audit-spec.md:93:### 5. Direction-shifting evidence — surfaced and missed
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/audit-spec.md:95:Did the slice surface direction-shifting evidence (per the dispatching project's §3.1 metaquestion + §3.4 long-horizon framing-axis question + cancellation-possibility per §1.11 aim)?
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/audit-spec.md:97:- Was there evidence in source the slice might have flagged but didn't?
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/audit-spec.md:98:- Was there evidence the slice flagged that, on your independent reading, doesn't actually shift direction (false positive)?
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/audit-spec.md:99:- Are there patterns across the slice's findings that, integrated, would shift direction even though no individual finding would? (This is the synthesis stage's job, but if you see it strongly, flag.)
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/audit-spec.md:101:## Output
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/audit-spec.md:103:Write to `~/workspace/projects/arxiv-sanity-mcp/.planning/gsd-2-uplift/exploration/0{N}-{slice-name}-audit.md` via apply_patch.
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/audit-spec.md:105:Output structure:
