.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:1:# Cross-vendor first-wave exploration of gsd-2 — common preamble
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:3:This is the **common preamble** prepended to each slice spec when an agent is dispatched. Slice-specific content lives in `slice-0X-*.md`. The agent receives: this preamble + the slice spec, concatenated.
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:7:## Your role and runtime
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:9:You are a focused cross-vendor reader of the gsd-2 codebase, dispatched as part of the dispatching project's (`arxiv-sanity-mcp`) first-wave exploration. You are running on GPT-5.5 with reasoning effort `high` via codex CLI. Take your time; the cost of careful characterization is acceptable. If you finish your slice in less than ~30 minutes you have probably moved too fast.
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:11:## Aim of this exploration
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:16:- A pre-pitched framing-mapping. Do not anchor your reading to any specific intervention shape (patcher / extension / fork / etc.) — those framings come later, informed by your reading and other slices.
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:20:If your slice's reading suggests the dispatching project's characterization-aim is itself wrong-shaped, flag as direction-shifting evidence in your output's open-questions section.
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:22:## Working directories
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:25:- **gsd-2 source (read-only target):** `/home/rookslog/workspace/projects/gsd-2-explore/` (shallow clone). Read source + README directly. Verify file existence by `ls`/`find`; do not assume specific files exist.
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:27:## Output discipline
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:29:- **Write via `apply_patch` only.** Do not write anywhere outside the output path your slice spec specifies.
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:30:- **Output target path** is given in your slice spec under "Output."
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:31:- **Do not modify gsd-2 source.** You are reading; not editing.
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:32:- **Final action must be the apply_patch write.** Do not run further tool calls after writing output (avoids the codex `--output-last-message` clobber issue).
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:34:## Calibration discipline
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:37:- **Cite source for each substantive claim** (`file:line` or `path/to/file`). Reader should be able to verify your claims by following citations.
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:39:- **Do not adopt the dispatching project's vocabulary** if you encounter it leaking through gsd-2's documentation; report what you see using gsd-2's own terms or neutral terms.
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:40:- **If you encounter material outside your slice's scope but flag-worthy**, note in your open-questions section; do not expand the slice.
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:42:## Cross-slice watchlist
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:44:The slicing intentionally focuses on five domains; some areas were considered and not made into their own slices. If any of the following appear central in gsd-2's source (not merely present), flag with citations in your open-questions section so synthesis can integrate:
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:46:- **Failure modes / debugging.** Specific debugging affordances (debug commands; structured failure outputs; recovery protocols).
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:47:- **Multi-user / collaboration.** Concurrent-editing primitives; team workflow surface; cross-user state sharing.
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:51:These belong in open-questions, not in your main answers, unless they directly answer a diagnostic question your slice already poses.
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:53:## Standard forbidden reading (applies to all slices)
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:55:You **must not** read the following before producing your slice output. Reading them would anchor your framing to the dispatching project's prior thinking — which is exactly what cross-vendor exploration is meant to avoid.
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:61:- `~/workspace/projects/arxiv-sanity-mcp/.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/` outside of your slice's spec + this preamble (other slices' specs may anchor you)
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:68:- Your own slice spec (`.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/slice-0X-*.md`) and this preamble
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:70:Slice-specific forbidden-reading additions live in each slice spec under its "Slice-specific forbidden reading" subsection (typically: prior slices' outputs).
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:72:## Standard output structure
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:74:Use this structure for your output (slice-specific path is in the slice spec):
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:78:slice: <N> (<slice name>)
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:84:# Slice <N> output — <slice name>
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:86:## (i) What I read
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:89:## (ii) Calibrated findings
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:90:<answer the slice's diagnostic questions with confidence labels and source citations per claim. Use a sub-heading per question (### Q1: ..., ### Q2: ...)>
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:92:## (iii) What I deliberately did NOT read
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:93:<scope boundaries; what's outside this slice; what readings would have anchored you and you avoided>
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/preamble.md:95:## (iv) Open questions surfaced
