.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/slice-01-mental-model.md:45:- A reader who has never seen gsd-2 should come away knowing what it is and who it's for, with concrete enough understanding to formulate substantive questions for slices 2-5.
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/slice-01-mental-model.md:48:- If gsd-2's self-presentation diverges substantially from what its source actually does (e.g., README claims X stance; source supports Y), surface that as direction-shifting evidence. Do not characterize gsd-2 against any category the dispatching project might have in mind — describe gsd-2 in its own terms.
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/slice-01-mental-model.md:50:## Pilot-specific note
.planning/gsd-2-uplift/orchestration/slice-01-mental-model.md:52:Because you are slice 1 (pilot), your output also informs the dispatching project's calibration of slices 2-5 prompts. If you found the slice-1 prompt itself unclear, ambiguous, or framing-leaky — flag in open-questions. The project will revise other slices' prompts based on your feedback before parallel dispatch.
